\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Frank Woolley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 34 Speedwell Street, Longton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And the year of you marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 1930.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Ashfield Road, Longton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how many years you lived in Edgefield Road in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I'm afraid not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember if you stayed in that house until 1918 or were there any moves in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh there's moves in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember where you moved to from Edgefield Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
The first address I can remember living in is number 8 Heathcote Street, as I can remember living in. So I must have been a baby when I left Edgefield Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you can't have lived there very long at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. And then the next address is Melvin Street.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how long you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I should be there 'til I'm about nine I should imagine, eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And then where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 57 Speedwell Street. And that's - that's where I stayed 'til I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you remember why the family made all these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well in them days they used to do, families could go anywhere. There was always houses empty you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you know why this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well - I couldn't say really. 'Cos I can remember in this row here, three or four houses empty at a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Couldn't people afford them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they could afford a them but they could move anywhere - but the reason why did move into Speedwell Street is when
 the family was getting bigger, had a three roomed house see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So as the family increased you need a larger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how many brother and sisters you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I had three brothers, seven sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So there was eleven children altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember in which order they came and the difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Me eldest sister. Then they've had me in nine month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what her name is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Me eldest sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Is she still alive?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, that's the one who's dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Florence. And then it come -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you tell me their names and the interval between each of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I seem to see - there must have been one in between see, that one was 
died. But - the next was after me. After me. Well I'm eighteen month older than her. And then there's Millie. Hers about - about sixty-one her is. And there is - must have been one - so that lad must have died between her and me I should imagine. And }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8338629\charrsid10123639 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8338629\charrsid10123639 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
 there's Hilda, sixty. There wasn't much difference between them who was there. And then there's Elsie. Hers fifty-eight. There's Les fifty-six. Let's see, who's next. Then there's Dol, I should imagine she'll be about fifty-four or five. Then there's - L
ily, that's the last. Hers fifty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So how old would your eldest sister have been now, three year and nine months older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, her'd have been seventy - her been seventy-three this March.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So there was twenty-three years between the youngest and the eldest in that case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it. That's it. That's it. Aye, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 He'd be about twenty-four when I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No,
 couldn't remember where he come - but I know as a child he was in the - he used to call it the workhouse at that time you know, this - dad used to have a - well it was a bit of trouble in the family, between me father's husband - me father's mother and I
 think he left it. Me grandfather. 'Cos I never knewed me grandfather. But I knew me grandmother. Any road, they come out here and set up home. Bit after when the lads was getting on and working you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where was your grandmother while he was in the workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She'd be - she'd be in there with them. At that time, aye, and then they came out and set home up together you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So was this your grandmother and her two sons, were there two sons?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, there's four - four sons. Four sons and one daughter.
