ressed up and we used to always have a suit and a new pair of shoes. Now them had got to last twelve month, you had no more in between you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they always new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were always new. Just at anniversary time. My mother used to buy material for 
the girls - have a dressmaker making them. But there was never nothing in between you know. Then had to do 'til next year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you had the one set of clothes and new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. That's it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well they were bought in Longton somewhere, I don't know. I know the house used to come from Sharps. Sharps shoe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8338629\charrsid10123639 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 shop in Stafford Street, Longton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You always had your shoes from there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, we always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8338629\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 hand shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you always had new shoes and new clothes just once a year for the anniversary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
That's it. Then we used to wear them every Sunday like. And then - when we had the new we wore them weekdays, we'd have to go to school in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you wore them a year as best and then the next year they were school clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, helped - help her a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you tell me what he used to help her with particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh aye. He'd do the cooking perhaps or - well he'd help in the kitchen any road. Aye, and then he always used to make the beds. Oh aye. Oh aye, did it - well he'd got to do - especially when the family was growing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he do the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, make the fires. Oh he wasn't a bad old stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about decorating and repairs to the house and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh he used to have to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your father dressing the children and undressing them or was this something that used to be your mother's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I daresay he'd undress us at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he read you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, can't remember that, never had any stories read to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not by your mum either?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Not as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I don't - see - aye, might have tell us a story or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your father bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I've seen him bath 'em. Seen him bath 'em oh aye when they were new. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where did you have your baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh un front of hearth. In the kitchen. No baths in houses then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, take us out - we had walks but that's all. Nothing that cost money, 'cos he hadn't got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he ever look after you while she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well - mother never went out a lot, only shopping. Perhaps Saturday nights they'd go out - down Longton and they might take about a couple or so half pints you know time they'd done the shopping same as they used 
to do. That's the only time she ever went out - 'til - 'til the family grew up of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have any particular chores you had to do regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I used to do a lot for my mother. I know - well me father used to get up to go work you know
 - that - they had to go - they went out about five o'clock in the morning you know. Well - and then - they always had a good breakfast, cooked, on things at front of fire you know and tin bonnet up to it. But my father - we had always got a big pickle ja
r of cabbage on table, I can remember it. Well he always had this for his breakfast. And I used to get up without anybody knowing it. I've cleaned the brass today before mother's get up. I used to get up with me father and then go back again see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, I didn't have to do it. I just did it. Oh aye, we did lots, me and me and me elder sister, did lots of - odd jobs about the house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How long did you continue to do this, did you do it after you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh no, not after I left. Because the others were growing up then and he used to do it. 'Course before we left school used to have a paper round or - I used to go round selling pikelets, Sunday mornings. Then I would be about twelve.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your brothers and sisters having special jobs in the house that they used to have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well we never used to have to do anything. They did though. Aye. We did do it. Didn't have to do it. But - don't remember me mother or father to do these things. And I've heard 'em refuse and go out playing. But more often than not they would do it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult, did you ever help the babies to dress or eat or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, no. Nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Your mother always did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the younger children ever help you at all with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well we should be in bed about nine o'clock, but more often than not we was very tired and ready to go at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I suppose we tucked in bed early then. Incidentally I went to school when I was three you know. Oh aye, went to school at three in t
hem days. I can't remember this but - he said I st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8338629\charrsid10123639 ill had bl-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
used on when I went to school. And I used to have a dummy and that and have it stuck in - well that's what they tell me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother put you to bed or anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well - aye, they put us to bed when we were young but - we used to get upstairs ourselves more often than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how old you were when you first started going to bed by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, can't - well I'd be about - five or six I suppose, go upstairs on your own, get in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you share a bedroom or a bed with anyone else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh when I was young I'd share a bed with me sisters. When I was very young. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 There'd be quite a lot of you in one house at one time wouldn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh there would, there'd be - let's see, there was nine of us then, be eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how you did sleep, the sleeping arrangements for the whole family? Wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 'd sleep in what bedroom with who? Did your mum and dad have a bedroom to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
They had one on their own. And then I - 'course when we got - I don't know how we slept, I know I slept with me sisters when we was young. Of course when I'm getting on have a bed on my own, me and Les I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you sleep in the same bedroom as the girls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So the boys were in one and the girls in another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But your mum and dad always had a room to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You said you had your baths in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of a bath was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Like one of them - tin baths. They used to call them bath tins. How big would they be - I'd say they were about four foot long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have special days of the week that you had a bath, can you remember how often you had a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye - generally Friday night. Only once a week baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have clean clothes to put on when you had a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Every time we had a bath we changed. Every time. Aye. Friday night. That's it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember where the family had the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there ever any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where did your mother do her cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did she cook on, was it a range or was it gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well we used to have
 - a - a - them old fashioned fire grates. Baking tin and that used to have - I think now - just spit on the front of it and a tin bonnet up. Used to make better - it was - the nice taste there you know that had. Well the joint they used to put in the ove
n. When I was very young there wasn't even a gas stove you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did she have a gas stove as well as this range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They had a gas stove later on. Oh aye, used to have oven, used to put the joint in that oven. Used to keep it lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you liked the food that was cooked in the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh aye. Was this tin bonnet and ingles stunt. Used to cook it lovely you know that had. I'll bet your father can remember them, tin bonnets and ingles. And sometimes when you used to cook it - you'd perhaps p
oke coke or two up and coal on plate and you'd just put this coke out, it didn't make any difference, you'd got to eat it. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When was breakfast eaten, what time of day and what members of the family were present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well of course me father'd be at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your father have breakfast by himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, well - same as I say, they had to be up at five o'clock to be at work at seven in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did your father used to eat for his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh bacon and cheese and picked - cabbage or a bit of - we'd always got a big stone jar of cabbage or pickled onions. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So he always had a cooked breakfast before he went to work did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, mother always used to get up, cook his breakfast and then off bed again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you children eat for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well probably'd have bacon and cheese or that. Oh we didn't do missing feeding I'll tell you. It was good rough plain food you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If you didn't have bacon and cheese what would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well perhaps we'd have a bit of good dripping - used to go to the hotel fetch dripping in a big basin you know. Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The hotel kitchens used to sell bowls of dripping then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Of course they had. That was lovely dripping that was you know,
 pork dripping and beef dripping. Better than any butter. Oh toast and dripping used to be lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So this was the sort of breakfast you used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you have to drink with your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have anything different for breakfast on certain days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. I'll tell you about Sundays now. Well in them days, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 market}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  used to be open 'til eleven o'clock Saturday nights you know. Most of those women with big families go down the market, yo
u'd bring a load of meat up - and perhaps a big plate of fish - cod fish. I knew my father always used to get up Sunday morning. And wrapped this cod fish in a rag, put it on a big pot on fire, boil it, then it was damned big plateful of - beef and sausag
e. The whole family this was. And then they used to dish it out and put this cod fish on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Eat the fish with the meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Eat fish with the meat, it used to be lovely. Oh - this codfish used to be boiled. It used to be nice flakey fish. We used to ha
ve it Sunday mornings regular that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of meat did you have with your sausage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Steak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you had steak and sausage and fish together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, and the gravy used to be lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Your father used to cook on the open fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Yes. Cook on open fire, tin bonnet. Used to have a great big plate - one of them big oval plates you know, then he used to dish it up when it was done. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 This was a regular breakfast on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Sundays, aye. Used to be good - see get a ton
 of meat then for little or nothing in the market at that time of night when it was late. And good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I've never heard of anybody eating meat and fish together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh you want to try it sometime. I'm not kidding you. You get a bit of codfish and a bi
t of meat and - I'm not kidding you the gravy'll be lovely. You would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what you used to have for your midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I used to have some real good midday meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you come home from school for your dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Come home from school. We used to have some good stew. My mother could knock a meal up with anything you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She was a good cook was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She was. Well as big a family as it got I well say this we were fed well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You never went without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 We didna. Oh aye, we were fed well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what you used to eat at your evening meal, what did you call your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you call your meal }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you have for your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh perhaps bit of bread and butter and jam or - used to be a lot of black treacle eaten in them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So with having a big meal at lunchtime you didn't have a particularly big meat at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you had your big meal of the day in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it. Oh aye, you got some real tuck-ins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about your midday meal on Sundays, was that different than the weekday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, be - be a joint perhaps or a piece of pork, anything like that you know. Aye, and a 
sweet at after. We never had a sweet after in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you had one on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, more often than not it was rice pudding you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was Sunday tea any different than weekday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, open a tin of salmon that day. Be them -
 be them big tall tins you know, not them flat tins same as they've got now. Aye, salmon and cucumber. Only used to put onion in this cucumber you know. Aye, and perhaps a bit of cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That was a sort of special Sunday tea was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well, we were fed well as big a family as we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember your mother or father baking their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. My father used to bake it many times. Father baked it. But he didna - he didna bake it regular. He'd perhaps knock a batch up - bakin
g up at weekend or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would he do this every weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well, not every weekend. But he has done it. Aye, it used to be nice, I remember I used to like it new. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he bake that in the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In his oven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they make their own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Aye, made all their own jam, damson jam and - but they used to buy a lot, you'd buy a big two pound pot then for about a tanner and perhaps cheaper than that in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So it was very nearly as cheap to buy it as it was to make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about bottling fruit or vegetables, did she ever do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about making pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, making - always making pickles. I tell you, there was always a big stone jar or pickles and - used to p
ickle onions and cauliflower together and then this pickled cabbage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She always did this herself did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh always, aye. And we used to love it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever make any homemade wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. But - every weekend - we was always dosed. Every weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 With what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well perhaps sometimes it'd be - big jar - jug - he'd cut two pair of lemons up and put a couple of packets of Epsom Salts in. That's what they used to call lemon tea. And we had to have that whether we wanted it or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They always made this themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Always made that them - or that senna tea. That - that - I couldna take that stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they make that themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Or li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 orice powder, we were always dosed with something weekend.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Every weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Every weekend we'd got to have a dose of opening medicine. Whether we needed it or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about beer, did they ever make their own beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh my father's made tons of herb beer you know. Oh yes. I
t used to be lovely. I've seen him - I've seen - yes, I've seen it pop off in - when it's been in the prantry. Blown up the bottom the bottle. Aye, used to - he used to make a lot of homemade beer, dandelions and nettles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he ever sell it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, sell it, it used to be a penny a bottle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It was a good brew was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, it was a good brew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother and father ever grow any of their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, they never had a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So they had to buy them did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh my father had a garden later on in years down here you know. He grew his own vegetables then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was it an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When your parents had to buy them did they buy tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well we always used to buy fresh vegetables - from greengrocers, there's always plenty about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they buy fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What fruit we had, we didn't have a lot of fruit. Aye, couldn't afford, not fruits on the table same as there is now you know in
 no houses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So they just used to buy vegetables did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever keep any livestock of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Yet our back yard is always full of hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Whp's were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you didn't have any of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. But I could always get one cheap though - if I'd have wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how many times a week you had meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh used to have some kind of meat every day. See, a stew or sommat. Unless we had fish. See I tell you Sunday
 morning we used to have fish and meat and all. Oh when - when they - used to go down market you know when I were younger my mother - they'd always bring a damn big bag of they - toffee fishes, they used to be six, eight a penny them had you know. Well th
e
 home, biggest part of toffee was four ounce a penny. Well at market you could get this - like boiled sweets - you like fishes or fruit drops - six ounces a penny. And then we always used to have them Sunday morning and perhaps an orange or something like
 that. Oh they knowed how to shop. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You didn't seem to go short of much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Went short of not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever get any extra meat any time such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh my father's had many a rabbit from pub off poachers. 
Oh aye. Perhaps a price of a pint of beer he's brought a rabbit off somebody who's a bit stuck. Oh they used to take 'em in pubs you know, rabbits, to sell. Aye, sell them, have a pint or a couple of pints for one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember who he used to get them off, was it any person in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, there's a fair lot of poachers about here. We had. They used to come round selling them Sunday mornings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Knocking in your doors?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Aye, got 'em slung over the shoulder. He'd g
o out all Saturday night perhaps and - all Friday night and he's come round. Oh aye, did that - regular. And watercress they used to come round with, they used to get - gather watercress and come round with it in a basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And knock on your door again and sell it that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Used to have Sunday night's tea quite often on watercress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you ever remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I couldna say as I did. I canna say as I ever saw her go short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you never went short either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember your father having more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. No. There always seemed to be enough food for us somehow or other, I don't know how they did it but they did do it. 'Course the colliers wage then was only about thirty bob a week you know. For six days. But they used to manage somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, used to do what we want. We wasn't restricted at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a little bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh we just what had what we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You weren't forced to eat anything you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What was your parents attitude if you ever left food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they'd want to know what - is there anything up with our health then I suppose. There wasn't much left I'll tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it or did you have t
o wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh no, we used to ask for it when we wanted it, salt, pepper, o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 r}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, if we wanted one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If there was any left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you expected to eat in a certain way, were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Just - just as we wanted. If we wanted to spoon it up we'd spoon it up, if we wanted to use a knife and fork we used it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about bringing toys or books to the table, could you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. We never had - didn't seem to have many toys to tell you the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you didn't bring them to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anytime. We never used to ask permission to leave the table. No. We'd finished used to get up and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When you'd finished or did you wait for everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When I'd finished if I wanted to getup I could get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You just got up when it suited you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Those that are in. 'Course - there was a few went out when we started work, used to come in various times to their meals you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But if all the family was in did you all sit down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have particular places at table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Sit anywhere. Me father had got a particular place, that was always in the armchair. Anybody had that, when he was in. Me mother'd always got one of them rocking chairs, that 
was her chair. But I used to get in 'em when he was out, when he wasn't there you could sit in 'em then but - soon at it's mealtimes or anything like that they always sit in them chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And you could sit anywhere you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anywhere we liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How was the meal served, who served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Mother used to - I've seen me father cut joint up many times Sundays. Seen him carve it up, father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember how hour mother would serve the meal, in what order she'd serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - put -
 having potatoes and dish them on plate and then - if we'd got a rabbit stew or anything like that put the rabbit on and perhaps stew and - roots and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What order were you served in, who was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, served in any order. Any order, it didna make no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When the younger children were small where did they sit before they could feed themselves, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The younger children? Oh well, I think they used to have one of those high chairs. You know, wit
h a what sit across. Aye, like a - used to be a little table on it, at the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they brought to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who used to feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well mother used to feed them but, of course - perhaps it might be before she give us our dinners or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But she always fed the younger ones did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember at what age you started sitting at the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - I've always sat at table as long as I can remember. So it must have been early age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember at what age the youngsters were brought to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I - as soon as you'd sit on a chair properly and - perhaps about four - five - four. As soon as we could sit at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When you were all in the house did you all always have your meals together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You never had staggered meals with there being so many of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you enjoy your mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I did. I tell you we used to have some real tuck-ins. I don't know how the hell they 
used to make a dinner out of some things we used to have. It beats me. I mean, no money. Where these - when you're come from school - I used to come up Albert Street and I ain't a kidding, you could smell dinner - 'cos summertime they always used to have 
t
heir doors open - you could smell dinner coming all the way up the street to your home. Everybody seemed to have a good stew on or something of that. 'Course a same as I say it was cheap then you know. And they knowed how to dish it up then they did. The 
real good cooks, a good many of them. No. They knowed how to do it Carol. They did. I can never - I can never remember going short of any food, never. No.
