 took our own part. Oh aye, while we were in school anyway. Mind you - they were strict in one sense - we'd always got to go Sunday school. We had to go Sunday school in the afternoon, then we used to have a star card and mark 'em. Well they'd want to see
 that star card whether there was a mark on or whether it was bobbed or anything like that. Aye, used to have a star card you know and then - when you went to Sunday school you give it your teacher and teacher drop you - drop you a star in. Aye.
