Well I remember I had to carry that - in a little coffin, used to carry them then you know to the cemetery. Aye. I believe that was carried. Don't remember a hearse coming up nor nothing of that. Only a coffin you know. That's what they used to do 
with them when they died very young you know then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who attended this funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I never went. I suppose mother and father went, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what sort of mourning clothes ere worn in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh it always used to
 be black. You were supposed to wear black about twelve month after anybody died you know. It seems I never remember anybody dying in our family 'til I'd grown up. Bar that baby of course. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you ever taken out visiting friends, relations or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
I never take - I was never taken but I used to go myself. Me aunties and me grandmother's and all them places but - never went as a family. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You used to go and visit by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 With your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. I used to go shopping for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 Oh I didn't go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you go with your mother when she went shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No, never went with me mother shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not even when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not - not unless he's - oh he's maybe taken us a walk occasionally. Aye. Might take us a walk or two, aye. Can't remember going anywh
ere special with him though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of things did you used to do on these walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well we just walked round, that's 11 - nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anywhere special where you used to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Nothing special - in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you ever remember any special outings, any day trips or Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I can remember the special outing we used to have at chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What were they like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Sunday school treats, they used to be very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But not with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not with our parents, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. I were eighteen before I saw sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You can never remember going away for a holiday as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Never at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you never go for day trips or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, went a day trip. We used to go far as Rudyard, that'd be about eleven mile. But - we used to hire a pony and trap then you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 This was your mum and dad was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. And family. We used to hire - and it used to be ten or eleven m
ile, that was a favourite trip, Rudyard. We always reckoned that - that used to be a red letter day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you do then, what made it a red letter day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh when we got there used to have a bit of tea then - he'd generally take us on a boat on t
he lake. Aye, that might happen at the weeks holiday time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you never went much farther than Rudyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh never went no farther than Rudyard. Not while we're young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you tell me how you used to spend Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I used to do anything get a copper or two Saturdays. Like taking coal out for this coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 yard you know. Used to get perhaps three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence or four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
pence, well it was a lot of money then. Saturdays, then I remember Saturday nights we used to sell - used to sell papers. I used to sell papers in the week and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 To make your pocket money up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I didn't - I used to give it me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 All of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well may perhaps keep a penny or tuppence. Oh aye, the - if you earned a tanner your mother - generally had about five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12726591\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence on it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you all have little jobs at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Me eldest sister used to - go round this - well I used to go with her Saturdays - Saturday afternoons and Sundays - selling pikelets and oatcakes in a basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did she make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, me father made 'em. Father used to make 'em on Friday nights, that was the time he was on compensation with his eyes. He got - night stand as he used to call it. Through working in the pit that was you know. Aye, and he used to m
ake this batch of pikelets and oatcakes and we used to get round with a basket and get shot of 'em. I can remember they used to be seven for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence. Good thick'uns and all they were. Aye, me mother always used to re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
kon he used to make the rent out of 'em, what he gained out of 'em. 'Course}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
father's on come then, he'd only bet getting about a pound, perhaps less than a pound a week. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, do anything, get roughing it about streets, playing football or - anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well we used to go there morning. I didn't used to go at night time. But we always used to go Sunday school. Mondays and that - mornings and afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have different clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I got a s
pecial suit for Sundays. But we used to have to change 'em when we went to play football after we'd been chapel. Oh that suit used to have to last twelve month, there's nothing in between. That was the Sunday suit for the year. When next year come round t
hey started wearing that for weekdays and - new suit for Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You used to play football on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would this be after chapel in the morning or in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 After chapel in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anything else you used to play as well as football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh at night time in them days they - used to have gas lamps there in the streets you know, the gas lamps, not these electric. Oh used to congregate about twenty or thirty lads - got under those gas lamps you'd play all sorts 
of games. Game they called prison bars or rally-o. Used to run up - run up and down chasing somebody daft.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What was this prison bars, what did you have to do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well you used to make a den or something and if anybody had stopped you you'd p
ut them in these dens in the - in this den and they had to stop there 'til one of the opposing side came round and relieved them. Oh there was all sorts of games. Jumping on backs and - we used to get a game going about five on 'em get down and then there
 
used to be five on this side and then they'd jump - and oh there's five got down on their backs you know. Five backs so play all day. Oh we used to - they used to enjoy theirselves, 'course they'd got any money to spend then you know. But they always seem
e
d to be happy, children did. Yes, played all kinds of games. Marbles under the gas lamp we used to play at night time. The girls'd play this hopscotch you know. Oh used to be about twenty or thirty assembled together at night time always under those gas l
amps. Regular meeting place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your parents ever thinking it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. They didn't mind what they did Sundays as long as you're out of the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Very rare. Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When they did what denomination was it, where would they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Methodist. They'd always go there anniversary time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The church anniversary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Or of course if he - when they had to go funerals or memorial services and he'd go then. Never made habit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go to church with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You used to go morning and afternoon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Morning and afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of things did you do in Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
We used to hear the scripture and - all kinds of things. But that little chapel as I went there's always something nearly every night you know. What they call Band of Hope, used to be games and - and - in schoolroom. And then - we had our B
rigade. Drilling for Brigade and bugle practice - I used to play bugle. Boys Brigade. Then I used to go camping at - once a year. From chapel. Of course that was when I - after I'd left school that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what sort of Sunday school outings there would be when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I used to have some good 'uns. They used to take us in brakes - you know, brakes and - or else ponies and traps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What's a brake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 A brakes a big long - it used to be a big - like a big lo
ng carriage, used to be seats then, perhaps about twenty or thirty you see as drove with two horses. Well they would take you anything up to ten mile. Perhaps Sandon or Rudyard. Cheadle. That's what they used to give you for the Sunday school treat. And t
h
en they give you a good tea and - we used - they used to get races up, give you little prize. There was running and all kinds of - all kinds of sport. Oh we used to look forward to it weeks ahead - Sunday school treat. Nowadays they dunna bother. Doesn't 
matter where they go, they dunna enjoy it as much as we used to enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you really enjoyed your Sunday school outings did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in, you said later on you j
oined the Boys Brigade, but was there anything else you used to do connected with chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not even when you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not when I got older, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the chapel have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Well - the same as I say, there was sommat - sommat on at chapel - in the schoolroom perhaps four or five times a week. Same as - Band of Hope and they used to have discussions a
nd - about different things and - then they used to play games in chapel, that used to be mixed, boys and girls and all you know. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was grace ever said at meals in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Yes. Aye. And that - that's a funny thing, I've always said me prayers every night. Even now. I never miss. I never miss saying my prayers nights and I never miss saying our Father which art - in the morning when I waken up, I always say that. But I say 
- say a different prayer at night time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you've always said your prayers have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Always said me prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. But my father never went bed unless he said his prayers. My father'd been 
out drinking - he'd get down - he'd always get down on his knees, hands and knees. 'Course I don't do that when I say my prayers, I say 'em in bed. But not me father, he always used to be side of bed, we've fell over him many a time when we've gone in mot
her's room. Even when he'd had too much beer he'd get down and always say his prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother say her prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Mother said hers as I can remember. If her did her said 'em in bed. But me dad always used to get down on his hands and knees.
 Always. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your father ever taking an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well not a big interest but - he was always a big Labour man, me father was. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you know why particularly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I don't. No I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, can't say I know what his views were. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh mother never used to take no interest in politics - wasna clever enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did she not have any particular views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No particular views.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember your mother and father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I don't think - I don't think women had got a vote then had they? Don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your father voting in an election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Remember him voting in two or three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And he always voted Labour did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Always voted Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In some places at that time a lot of men felt they risked losing their jobs if they voted differently from their empl
oyers, do you know if your father ever felt himself under any pressures of this sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Never. Never. Father was always a collier and I think - in them days ninety percent of the colliers voted Labour. Perhaps higher percentage than that. But I - I can - never pressurized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he belong to a political party, was he a member of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he work for any one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I don't remember. He used to go to these meetings you know when the - you kn
ow same as the meetings they do have before election. He used to attend them. But I don't think he was a member.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember him ever doing any particular work for the party during election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he ever take part in political activity other than at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When your parents were not at work how did they spend their leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well me father come home from work - might do odd job or two round the house but - if he'd got
 any money left at night time he'd go have a drink or two. But that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. In then - in them days they did - didn't have any money for beer in the week. Only just a - drink or two at weekend. No, never any money for b
eer in the week. You'd see this - men gongregating at the street corners and all that kind of thing, rattling about anything. No, there - there wasn't much drinking done in the week. But the weekend - there was plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what your father and mother used to do of an evening when all the work was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did they used to pass the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well father'd have paper - pick paper up and read 'til bedtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What would your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well she always seemed to be busy doing a bit of sommat. If her want her'd sit about else just - lie on the couch or sommat of that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother ever have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Nothing at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She didn't belong to any women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. There wasn't - there wasn't many women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s clubs at that time. No. Mother used to go out - perhaps go visit her sister or her - me - her mother or perhaps a friend or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did she always go by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 More often than not. Perhaps she'd take the youngsters with her, the very young 'uns you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember your mother going out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, canna say as I could - not - not while we were young. Mind you well now they'd have had a real good time, m
e mother did when we were all grown up. Mother and father went away every year. Oh they went for years and years. When we started work, you know, get - but - while we were very young really they didn't have much life. Bar stopping in the home you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You say your father used to go to the pub of a weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And in the week if he'd got any money left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother never go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well the only time me mother used to go was when they used to go shopping Saturday nights.
 Perhaps she'd go shopping with one of the neighbours and - they might call in a pub when they'd done the shopping, perhaps about a couple of half pints, something like that. I can remember 'em doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where would they be held at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Chester used to be the favourite race course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Very little - very little. He wasn't a big gambler me father wasn't. He'd pe
rhaps have a - odd sixpence, what he used to call a tanner. And I mean he hadn't used to have a lot of money to gamble with you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he go to football matches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh he liked to - he used to like go - to go to football match, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did he have a bet on the pools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well pools weren't out when we were young. No. No. They didna come into being 'til about 19 - about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
metricconverter}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 1930 in}}}1930 in{\*\xmlclose} a big way you know. Used to have those - fixed odds coupons then. Aye. He might have a tanner or a bob on a coupon, fixed odds you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So apart from horse racing and football matches he didn't take part in any particular sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother and father belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh me mother's never out of savings clubs. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of savings clubs did she belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 There used to be a club called the Lightwood Club. You could save anything from three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  three}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence a week to a pound a week. But my mother always managed to - get a bob or two for weeks times, that's
 at holiday time like. Oh aye. Because in them days the colliery used to have a week off. With no pay you know. Never used to get a ha'penny pay, that w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s holidays they had they used to have to stand it theirselves. Well this saving club my mother'd always
 got that covered. She'd says perhaps save a shilling a week. Well that was all of fifty bob for the year. That was more than a man got wages then. The biggest - biggest part of them never got above thirty-five shilling a week you know. And that was recko
ned decent wages then in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So would you have to keep house and pay everything that's necessary for the house out of that thirty-five shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You would, less than that. The men'd want their pocket brass out of that and one thing and an
other. Used to have to keep it less than that Carol. Oh aye. I don't know how they did it but they did do. 'Course things were very cheap you know. Very cheap.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother belong to any funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Funeral clubs? Oh aye, her'd got us all
 insured. Oh aye. Well they could insure you then for a penny or tuppence a week, it'd cover you for your burial.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And you were all in these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, all in them. Aye. And - we used to pay this dispensary to doctors you know. That was to cover us
 for sickness. That was before this National Health come on. He used to come on one night from doctors collecting this - what they called dispensary money. I think it used to be about three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was that for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Used to cover the family at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I never had any trouble. No, used to get on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there any one of them that you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not really. Of course I'd only got one brother, the others were sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there any one of your sisters that you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well - I never had a brother 'til I was twelve. Because I'm - I'm twelve - I'm twelve year - I had another brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So it would be sisters mainly when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. And then it'd only be about a couple of them wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When you were a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who was your particular friend when you were a child, was it your sister or neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - I used to - I never used to play with the sister outside, I - if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 
 I did that I should be called sissy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  then in them days. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  I mean when you were young at school, not after you'd lect school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. I mean only be
ing school, I used to play neighbours children, same as I tell you, congregate together night time, daytime, get a - one of those little rubber balls and get kicking it about in fields. Aye. Never used to play with my sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not outside where anybody could see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You said you played in the street around the gas lamps, did you play in the yard or in any to the other children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you ever allowed to play indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. I never - never remember playing indoors. Unless it was a game of ludo or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you allowed to take your friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Yes. Take anybody in. We did what we liked in them days, used to come and march in. If you'd got a mate they'd just open the door and march in an
d ask if you're coming out to play. I mean never used to bother with any - knocking and one thing and another. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You used to play prison bars did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Aye, or rally-o - anything. Marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Didn't never used to take any notice whether we got dirty or not. But - if we went in dirty we'd got to have - we'd got to have a d}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 am}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ned good wash before we went bed.; Never knew baths you know in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you did have your bath in a tin bath on Fridays didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you allowed to play with anyone that you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I was allowed play with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there no one that your parents tried to discourage you from playing with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Only the - Boys Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How often did you go to the Boys Brigade meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When were they, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Perhaps they'd be Tuesdays and Thursdays generally. T
hen we used to - we kind of used to get a parade about, you know, parade about the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Every weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not every weekend but more often than not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you do on these parades?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 We just marched round that's all. Yes, same as sol
diers. Kettle drum and bugles and - we might do us - have a ramble as far as Weley Rocks or anything like that. For the day you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you had outings with the Boys Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Aye, but - they never used to give us tea nor nothing like th
at the same as they did at chapel you know. It was just a walk. Oh aye. Aye, used to get bits of games, paper c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
ases and all that kind of thing. Dropping paper and you had to - you - we used to run miles for this paper. You used to drop it different places you know and you'd got to follow it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Can you tell me what you did with your free time while you were still at school, did you have any special hobbies or did you collect anything or do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, did no gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you keep any pets, did you have a dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, we never had a dog. I had a couple of rabbits once I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you still at school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, I soon got fed up with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Only for - what you - jack sharps. N
ever went - I used to get a lump stick and a piece of cotton or something on, just tie a grub on, chuck 'em in and catch these jack sharps. That's the only fishing I've done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, I had a bike. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you go any distance, did you ride with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
I used to - ride with my friends. Oh I'd go a mile or two out on them. But that bike as I got used to be a ladies bike, I used to have to manage with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you go for many walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, used to do a lot of walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who did you go with particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh friends, we used to congregate when we'd finished - chapel in the morning. Perhaps nine or ten on us would take off then for a good walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 All boys would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 All boys. Walk ro
und country 'til dinnertime you know. And gone have our dinners then off chapel again for afternoon session and then we might go another walk then at after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go to the cinema or to any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I went to cinema, I always used to like - I used to like to go to pictures - every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 While you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What day of the week did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I used to go any - any day like as long as I'd got the money. 'Course you'd get in for a penny then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you save your weekend pocket money then to get you through the week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well sometimes I'd go a - might be lucky and go errand - errand or two for somebody and they'd perhaps give us a penny or tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, I went to the theatre, I used to like got to the theatre. Specially when there's a - a - a variety show on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How often did you go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of acts were there at this variety show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 There used to be some real good turns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was it more of a music hall do you think than a theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It was a variety theatre. It used to be the Empire at Longton we used to go. Then we used to go Grand Theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Arnley. And then the - the theatre Royal at the time they used to put on these musical comedies and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 To see the musical comedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, and good. No. No Nanette. Lady be Good. Desert Song. Wild Time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they done by local companies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh no, no. Done by the professionals, used to travel up and down the country you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember anybody at the time who came to the Theatre Royal that was famous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, not in the musical - not in musical com
edies. Oh I saw who is it - Evelyn Laye there. In musical comedy and - eeh what's her name. That's who in that - in The Arches. Oh Jessie Matthews. That was real good. And at Longton theatre used to have those - variety artists you know, same as }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 n
ame - conjurers, some good conjurers there, Jimmy Drew. They used to be a real good one in days you know. And - who else did I see. Then there's Doctor Body used to go with us, all electrical stuff you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you used to enjoy going to these theatres and music halls did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there any cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well there's one - that's generally along - by Sander Palace, he used to have pictures and then a variety artist in between. So when you went there you used to have a picture, a silent picture you know and a - a turn in between, a live turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In between pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In between the pictures, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember who would be famous in the cinema when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh they used to have a real lot, there'd be P
earl White. Aye, he was one of them. I forget what they were on the - be some good real silent films.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you go on for music during the film?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well there used to be a pianist there. Aye, a pianist on the stage plays through all the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And then this variety artist while you were waiting for the second film to come on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Well it used to be very cheap, you could get in for a penny you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was this children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s matinees or general times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Us children get in for a pe
nny at night time. And the theatres at Arnely, they used to go up the gods up - there, this gallery, we used to call it gods, you could get up there for tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 To see a live show?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 To see a live show and some good artists. I've seen Layton and
 Johnson there. I've seen Vesta Tilly. Hetty King. Oh some real good turns there was. Real good artists. Marie Lloyd, hers been up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents give you picket money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, we used to make our own pocket money. Running errands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember about how much pocket money you used to get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
You mean afore I started work like? Oh - I can remember when I was still in school at - there used to be two brothers used to be up the colliery at Bucknell, Central colliery, used to work o
n the bank, the pit top like. Well I used to take their breakfast in the morning before I went to school, let's say half - it'd be at least a mile and a half there and a mile and a half back, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence a week. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You took their breakfast every day to Bucknell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 To Bucknell. And then at dinnertime, I used to take 'em lunch - dinner. Just down bottom of Lanfield Place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was that a pot factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Pot factory, yes. Used to take him a piece with a red hanky wrapped round it you know and knotted and - that was another three}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence a week. That was sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Why did they not take it with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I couldna - I couldna say. But - there used to be a lot of it about then you know. Oh there was any c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 nteens or nothing. I didn't expect they could get anything unless they come home for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did they have for their breakfasts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh I used to take them bacon and cheese or bacon and egg. Wrap it in - used to make sandwiches of it, then used to wrap it in - paper, not tissue 
paper, just ordinary newspaper and then wrap it in a - one of those red handkerchiefs. Oh aye, I did that for for a good while, take their breakfasts. Well they started work at six o'clock in the morning then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They never had breakfast before they went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
They mustn't have done. Then I used to get there before - I used to have to go to school at half past nine so I should have to be there for about quarter to nine to get back with school see. Oh we'd run miles for a penny in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You could buy a lot with a penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh buy four once of toffee. Real good toffees. I remember two favourite toffees. There used to be roast chew toffee, what they called roast chew and chocolate nougat toffee. That used to be four ounce - and never us
ed to go in for a pound - used to go in for a ha'porth you know, two ounce. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you earned sixpence a week so that was quite a lot of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you earn any more any other ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Mother - mother used to have some out of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you do anything else to earn pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh used to sell papers at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How much did that pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well if you made three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence - well if you made three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9705194\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
pence you know you wasn't too bad. Per week that was, not - not f
or one night. Every night. Oh you'd run miles for a copper or two in - we never used to take any notice. We used to really enjoy it. I remember - used to have to fetch they Sentinels from Longton Sentinel office. Oh and these lads, they used to fight to g
et these papers you know, to get first turn. Had many a scrap outside I expect the Sentinel Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the boys themselves pick up as many as they could carry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In them days you used to - dash out of that Sentinel office, up - up to Stanford Hill
, you used to have to keep shouting as you went up you know. Shouting - Sentinel. There wasn't no orders same as they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 People'd come to you in the streets and buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, they used to be a ha'penny each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You didn't take them to houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. There might be a few customers but - more often than not they were just sold as - in the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what else you'd spend your pocket money on as well as sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have to pay for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ourself to go to this theatre and the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So that had to come out of your pocket money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That used to have to come out of your pocket money. Sometime at weekend your father might give you it - ha'penny or a penny. But that's a
ll he can afford. I tell you they - we used to run about here - used to run about a mile to get a penny, yes. Perhaps you'd go an errand for some - run an errand for some people and come back, they'd give you a few sweets, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You didn't mind this, you'd run an errand for a few sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Of course we would. We would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did anyone outside your home ever help your mother to look after the house or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Suppose your mother was ill or confined to bed, how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well - I suppose me father used to look after us. 'Course when you was about eight then you used to look after yourself you know, you werena pampered, you could get around when you were eight year old in them days, well I could. Bit of bacon and 
cheese or anything like that you know. Then of course I'd got a sister older. We never had no help in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember what happened when your mum was having a baby, who would come and help then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well used to have a midwife in then. An
d father always used to get the - oh there was always neighbours. Aye, neighbours, they used to come in and bring a bowl of gruel. Or just little tit-bits you know. Only at those times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They wouldn't come in any other time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they'd come in i
f anybody was sick you know. Oh you used to walk in anybody's houses them days, knock and walk in never used to take any notice. There were some good neighbours about you know. Aye, I know my - aye, well understand there's always somebody taking these - t
hese tit bits in. Maybe aunties is come up or - perhaps cousins. But it used to be neighbours more often than not as used to look after 'em. 'Course the men couldn't afford to stop at home and look after them you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother always have her babies at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She had 'em all at home. Midwife used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who would a look after your mother after the baby was born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well same as I say, the neighbours used to. Oh aye. They used to come in turn us all over, tell us it was time w
e got up out of bed. They used to be in bed about nine or ten days I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So they were in bed quite a long time after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Aye, but there's always somebody in looking after 'em. I know my mother used to be in big demand for - laying folks out
 when they were dead, you know. Me mother had - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about undertakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh they all used to - oh there wasn't. When they died in them days the undertakers didn't lay you out you know. They didna. The neighbours did that job. My father used to see them when they were dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You say your mother was in demand as a layer out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh yes. Aye. Aye, they used to lay 'em out on a - like a big board, wax 'em and dress 'em, put a - big nightgown on kind of thing you know. Aye. Oh did a lot of that me mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did people just come and knock at the door and say ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Yes. 'Cos they - the neighbours they knewed all about - they hadn't used to get nothing for it you know. I don't know whether the undertaker used to treat 'em or not I'm sure but - I don't think they got anything for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would a neighbours just come along and say somebody had died and would your mother please go along and lay them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. That's it. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She'd have no qualms about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Had no qualms, she'd go straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When did the undertaker come in on it sort of thing? What did he have to do if they were already laid out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they didna take them in rest chapels then you know, when anybody died in them days they used to hav
e to stop in the home 'til they were buried. Oh aye, they used to - have like a wood table affair in the parlour, there only used to be a kitchen and a parlour you know, and - the dead person's always laid out - well when it was put in the coffin - it was
 put in the coffin and left there 'til the time for burial. Oh they never used to take them away same as they do now you know. Used to lay 'em out in the house and they stopped there until they were buried.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did somebody sort of sit with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Perhaps some of them did. Perhaps the Catholics would perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you don't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I never did it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They were just left there in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They were just left there in the parlour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they covered up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, they were covered up in a sheet 'til they were put in the coffin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You couldn't see them or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh you could see if you pull the sheets from over the head. See 'em all laid out and - when they put 'em in the coffin they lie there 
for anybody to come in and have a look at. They used to come in the house and have a look at them if they felt inclined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Anybody. Specially anybody that knows 'em - where they were living. Yes. Oh aye, see we never had these chapels - r
est chapels same as we've got now. Everybody had to stop in the house 'til they were buri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there a long period of time between death and the actual burial?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well generally it's about - between three and four days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So it wasn't particularly quick was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Of course if they'd got any bad disease when they died I think they used to - bring them in and box them up right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But still leave them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But still left them there. Aye. Oh if they died from bad - you c
ouldn't see them then you know. But otherwise they were left laid out in the coffin on a table. No coffin lid on. Then anybody as wanted to come and have a look at them they could do. They only put the coffin lid on just before the burial.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Suppose there were young children in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It didn't make any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So they'd see them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They'd see them if they wanted to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But if it was in a house where there was a big family they'd probably need to use the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh no, never used parlour when there was any death, you used to have to go in the back - back way. Come in the back way and go out the back way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So they wouldn't have any occasion to go into that room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But young children are very inquisitive aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Aye. Well they used to keep 'em out. I daresay many time they have been in and perhaps nobody's known.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were young children encouraged to look?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Same as I say, you please yourself - the - it's 
there for anybody who wants to. Oh the neighbours always used to come in, pop in have a look, especially just before they'm buried. Yes. Well - that's - that is what - that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, they had a lot of relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh used to be pretty often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You visited them and they visited you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. When we were children I used to like going round aunties, I might - maybe I might make a penny - a copper if they was inclined.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they had a fair amount. Everybody's friendly, especially neighbours in them days. Well all the neighbours where}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639  I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  lived were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If your parents went out to meet friends where would they meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They'd meet them at their home I suppose, isn't very often they went out together. Mother and father to meet friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they share the same friends or did your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they shared t
he same friends more - more or less. They used to know the same people. In them days in - if there was street same as this everybody'd know one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Wouldn't they venture very much farther?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So all their friends were more or less shared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Their neighbours they were more or less their friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they ever invited into your house, friends, neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They didn't want no inviting, they used to come in. And they could go in anybody else's house if they felt inclined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If they wanted to come in for an evening would they need inviting then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. They'd just drop in if they wanted I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And your parents did the same sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would they be offered anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh they'd always have a - be offered something to eat, perhaps a bit of bread and cheese or anything lie that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But they'd never go away without being offered something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would they be offered a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well there'd be - there'd be no drink in. I don't expect. If you was having any they'd be offered one I suppose. Or perhaps they'd fetch one in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or tea or coffee or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes, have tea, coffee, aye. Oh aye, they'd always be offered a drink of tea or coffee or cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever invite particular people to call round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would they make arrangements for people to come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Either relatives or friends used to drop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And - the neighbours also just used to drop in whenever the mood took them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And your parents used to do exactly the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever arrange to visit friends or neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. They called when the mood took them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They didn't need to have an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. 'Course perhaps there was two - one or two odd ones in the street 'cps they - well you knew they were a bit off you'd never venture go in them houses. See. You always knewed where you were welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 People tell us that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well that's - that's a fact, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What do you think your parents did with their friends, relatives and neighbours when they got together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who, me parents? I couldn't remembe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 r them having many get together}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 . Perhaps if there's anything on, same as a wedding or anything - they'd have a sing-song, anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would anyone play any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh, if there's - if there's anything on special if you hadna got a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 phone or owt of that you used to borrow one. Aye. Off one of neighbours if they've got one. If you got something on special. Gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 o
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 phone and records and all. I remember used to have a right sing-song then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And everybody would join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ever play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Never played any parlour games. Might be a game of cards, the men might, a game of crib or anything like that. Aye, card games. But - I don't know any other. 'Course bar children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid423807\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s games, there always used to be so many - in nearly every house they'd have a - either ludo board or a snake and ladder board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the adults play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Sometimes. But them used to be the two chief games you see, of the games, there was ludo and snakes and ladders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No parlour games of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Many people divide society into different social classes, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another and can you tell me what you thought the different levels of social classes were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I don't know. You may find some - perhaps what you'd call middle class when you went to school, you could always tell 'em how they were dressed and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What class did you consider you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh the ordinary working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You'd come across some people at school that were middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Perhaps their father had got a pretty good job, perhaps a manager or - anything like tha
t. Well you'd always be a cut above the working class if you got tem jobs you know. And it showed more often than not now they sent the children to school. Always a good suit on, a good pair of shoes, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you think of there just being the two classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
But - I'm saying a lot of them children - what I seen in the middle class is good mixers you know. I mean to say, used to play games with the - what we called the working class boys. Used to rough it with them just the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you think at that time of there just being two classes or would you say there were anymore besides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well that was the only two classes that - 'course we hadn't - knowed about the higher class of course. I never come across them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What do you term as higher class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I should expect them master potters sons or business folks sons and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you would think there were just three classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You thought of yourself as belonging to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well anybody as got just ordinary job. Same as colliers or - pottery workers. Brick workers. Or labourers, a brick labourer or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of people did you say belonged to the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I think when the parents had got a - higher paid job, same as manager - managing you see or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about the higher classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well them'd be business men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 s sons or master potter's sons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You would never have any contact with people of that class yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. I never had any - I can never remember a master potter's son - or a big business man's son coming to our school. Ordinary ele
mentary school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So if you met them you'd treat people of the upper class exactly the same as a working class person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Of course you should, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect to any particular people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I used to call schoolteacher sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What class would you think the teachers belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I should imagine middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would there be anyone else in the district you would call sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember who were considered the most important people in the district where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I can't think of anybody as important in our district. Important which way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Somebody that people were inclined to show particular respect to? Or perhaps some wealthy person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I can't remember any wealthy persons in this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you think that the clergy were important or your doctor was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, the doctors and - doctors and clergymen, you was - always used - showed them the greatest respect. Clergymen and doctors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you know why particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about shopkeepers in the area, would you think they were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not particularly. No, there was the - the corner shops, they'm always friendly to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you mix with these people socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of people would associate with the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
I never had any - I never had a lot to do with clergy because I used to go to Methodist church. In our Methodist chapel they always used to have the lay preachers practically every week. I'd see the minister there about - perhaps o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 nce a month or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 once in two month}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 . Otherwise -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What class would you say the Minister belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I'd say the middle class, ministers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you have any occasion to associate with him socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. You did send for the Ministers when anybody was seriously ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you didn't see much of him otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about your schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh well - we always respected them and - well they put the fear of God into us more often than not the teacher did in them days. Oh they had a 
- same as - they aren't the same as teachers today. These people today they don't seem to have the respect for the teachers as we had. I don't know why. But - we used to fear them teachers. Somehow or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you have no occasion to mix with hour teachers socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. Them teachers in them - them teachers in them days they - they werena frightened to give you that cane you know. They werena. They - they'd have you out in front of class and give you three or four strokes on the hand. But the
 - there's always one or two of teachers as never did you give cane but you're punished just the same, they had the - they used to send you to the headmaster. Then he used the cane. Oh aye - biggest part of the people been frightened of the teachers in th
em days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about the employers, what about your father's employers, your father was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 A collier. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What class would you say the pit owner was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh he'd the top class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Your father would never meet him socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. I don't think any of the work people met him social.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh they went - all kinds of people, all classes went to church or chapels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you would say that it was mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I should - yes. Never - no one particular group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have some of each class in your chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 We had the lot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You say the chapel used to have outings, would everybody go, the middle and upper classes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you'd mix with them would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, they'd mix with 'em then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you find there was any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I never found any difference. I never found any difference at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standa
rd of living, or would you say there were different standards for the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Aye, I think there was a distinction then. It's just according what sort of parents you'd got. Some - some of them unfortunately had bad parents then, drinking and w
hat instead of looking after food and that. But mine were different than that. But - I don't say as there was a lot of them about but there was some about. Used to think nothing but drink, and the children they'd go and scrounge a piece - perhaps a piece 
of bread and jam or - piece of bread and treacle from anywhere outside, I'd hear of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So there'd be a distinction even among the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Oh aye, I've seen 'em beg a piece many a time. Piece of bread, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think the group of working class people who looked after their families would consider themselves superior to the ones that didn't?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I should think so. Aye, I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So there was even a type of upper and lower class amongst the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well - I wouldn't say there's upper - upper class but - I've heard them decent working class people tell - tell the parents of them children's as couldn't seem to get enough food - I've heard 'em tell 'em off, I've seen 'em fight about it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They'd actually say they didn't think it was right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They didn't think it was right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were some families thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What particular type of person would you consider was rough in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye well th
ere used to be some aggressive folks about you know. Aye, they - always somebody wanting to be bossy over somebody else you know. Aye, theres - that's what used to cause a lot of arguments you know, used to be a hell of a lot of fighting in them days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Street fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh - street fighting. But I'll tell you what. It was seen as school this was. Them street fights always used to be - they're ostracized on a - if there's anybody kicking or anything like that. Oh it's same as having a fight at schoo
l. Anybody started - kicking instead of fighting with a fair fist they'd be practically sent to Coventry. The other people'd have nothing to do with that going on. Oh it was always a fair fight, always fists. Anybody - start kicking or anything like that 
or scratching or anything like - nobody got anything to do with 'em you know. It was the same with men when they come out of pubs when they started fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did they find to fight about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh you'd be surprised. All kinds of arguments, little arguments with people in a pub.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They'd fight over something quite trivial?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Something quite trivial. They would. I've watched 'em many hours in them fields there when they came out of pubs, especially weekends. Aye, they used to have a go, it used to be quite enjoyable watching them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there some families that were thought of as particularly respectable in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I should imagine there was, Carol. Aye, I should imagine there's some respected a lot more than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember any particular people amongst your particular group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
I can't remember anybody particular. I think my father was always well respected for one. And me mother. Aye, me mother always used to - always used to give a helping hand, if there's sickness or death or anything. Her was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 She was respected on account of this was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I should imagine her was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember there being a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers, would a 
craftsmen think of a labourer as rough and a labourer think of a craftsman as respectable? Would anything like this occur?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Well I think the - any craftsman'd think himself a cut above a labourer or anything like that, just as - it be just natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would a craftsman be considered respectable on account of him being a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
I don't know, it's just according what - what sort of temperament he's got, what no, this craftsmen was more respected than an ordinary labourer if a labourer kep
t within the bound you know. Of course there's some like craftsmen had used to think themselves superior you know. But there used to be good and bad - there's good and bad - good and bad labourers just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember your mother and father having the same attitude to people in different classes and groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I should imagine so. I should think they'd similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You can't remember any occasion when this would show itself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well - if it - only the working class. Yes. Oh that's quite definite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Why would she consider she belonged to the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The simple reason was one of the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would she think she was one 
of the working class because your father was a miner or because of the sort of work she used to do or because of the sort of house they'd got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I suppose so, yes. Aye. You must bear this in mind, them days there's more working class than anybody you k
now. There'd be whole street and all be working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember it being possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Not unless - not unless some working class family had somebody who'd particular brainy you know and got on like - if
 he got on he might lift his parents up as he got a bit older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever see this occur?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, I canna say as - I might have seen it occur but I've forgot. We hadna got the chance of education in them days. 'Cos we had to leave school at thirteen as you know. But - if anybody had got a brainy child they would try - they'd try and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would they still have to leave school at thirteen, what were the prospects of carrying on with their education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well it's just according getting exam to an
ything - I think they were hard to get them was. Perhaps - they'd be recommended by the teacher more than anything, you know, the head teacher and - I don't know how they went on after that. But - if a working class - parent - kept his lad on at school an
d
 he - and he - it'd be a big sacrifice for him. For the parent. Because all as they wanted in them days they wanted you to start earning at thirteen see. Which is only natural because there's no money about. I mean a lad could go anywhere for five or six 
s
hilling a week. That was a lot. Aye, that was considered a lot. Nut - when I was thirteen I started running moulds. Five and six a week it was. Mould running. I used to get sixpence a week extra for carrying water up to the - other makers, saucer makers a
n
d what - they made it six shilling. And then when I was fourteen - you were allowed to go in the pit then - you weren't allowed to go in the pit at thirteen you know in them days. You'd got to be fourteen. But then I went in pit at double the wages. Start
e
d off at twelve shilling a week then. I remember it. And that was a red letter day. But you'd got a job get in the pits then you know. You'd got to have a bit of backing off your parents or anything. If your parents was a good workman, he's lad had got a 
better chance - get in. But I did get in when I was fourteen any road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman in your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Nobody at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, can't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you remember seeing a policeman about when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Aye, they used - parade the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What was your attitude towards policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well we used to scatter when we used to see policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you were frightened of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother ever threaten you with a policeman when you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How would you think the policeman treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh there's some rough policemen about in the days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Rough in what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I've seen 'em trip drunken men up, that's the case, I've seen 'em do that you know. Aye. Trip 'em up. Then - if they're drunk and get a bit abusive perhaps and then they was run in. In them days he'd - he'd take 'em down. Aye, I've seen the pol
ice take 'em down Saturday night and then they'd be tried at the Monday morning you know. Perhaps fined about five shilling or seven and six. Well it wanted some finding that did you know. But you know what they used to do. They used to collect in the pub
 when they'd been - for his fine. Aye. I've known many a time - perhaps been fined five shilling, collected in pub, perhaps got about seven and six. Well pay his fine - he used to come and spend - he could get drunk with that half a crown.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So he'd pay his fine and come and get drunk on the remainder would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's it. Aye, it's been done above once that has.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think generally that the police were liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, I don't think they were disliked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you say you've definitely seen them work towards a case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Oh they used - especially Sunday afternoon on pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ching and tossing they used to come up -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  these - but those pitches and t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
osses always used to have a look out you know. See 'em all scatter. I can remember one Sunda
y afternoon - one was a detective and a police officer - and after they was tossing well this detective he'd got a cane. And one of the blokes was running off - he stuck this cane out and caught him round leg and tripped him straight up. And he did go wit
h a bump. Oh that used to be the game every time you know, tossing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What is pitching and tossing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well - pitch and toss - they used to make a little ring you know in the dirt - in the dirt, then put a mark in the middle. Perhaps a little white di
sc. And perhaps there'd be about ten of you. You'd pitch two pennies up - two pennies, each one'd pitch two pennies up to this mark. Well there'd be about - lets say there'd be half a dozen on you, there'd be twelve pennies would group. But the bloke near
e
st to that mark - he used to have the first toss up see. With those twelve pennies. They used to toss them two at a time, that was six two's. Well all heads has come down then he'd put them in his pocket. But say out of those twelve pennies there's - perh
a
ps he'd got eight heads out, of course he might have got eight tails, but they always put what had his - what dropped down heads he put them in - them is his own. And the tails, the next man who had got second to him, well he'd toss 'em up see. And that's
 
how it used to go on 'til all the pennies had been headed. But when you're tossing used to - all be in a ring and - perhaps a bloke'd have two pennies on his fingers - there used to be a stake holder in the middle of this ring and they'd give this stake h
older perhaps five shilling. Tell him get that on the crowd you know. Perhaps some'd bet three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
pence or sixpence or a shilling 'til the five shillings was made up. Maybe or ten shilling. Well they'd got to toss now 'til he headed 'em or tailed 'em. If they 
come down both heads they had ten shilling. If they come down both tails of the course the stake holder paid out them as had betted see. But - once you'd own five shilling stake and perhaps had 'em about four or five times on the trot - that's - That's en
d of school practically.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 This game was considered illegal though was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
It was illegal. It was illegal. Aye, used to have a - used to have a fellow watching. Used to be somebody watching out for the police. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What happened if you were caught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh well you had to go down police office, he's up at Monday morning again. And - more often than not that's the same procedure, you used to collect round to pay the fine. Able them as was in tossing. I think it was very profitable at times to get caught.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, saw a lot of landlord, he used to collect the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh not too bad. They wouldn't do anythi
ng to the house if they could help it you know. No. No, they wouldna do - very often you had to do it yourselves. 'Course they only used to be about - four shilling a week houses had then you know. If you're living in a house about five shilling a week it
's supposed to be a decent house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well you know - they'd always got a struggle to make ends meet. But they used to do it somehow or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you think about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I thought - I thought it wasna - in them days when I was about twelve year I thought there must be somebody - some clever management here somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 In your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Because of what they used to manage on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You said before you used to eat very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh we did eat well, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And you were surprised at this because it was obviously a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It was a struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Never remember him being ill. I can remember - I can remember him being on compensation. 'Course then he had - he must have had a hell of a struggle then, I don't know how the hell he managed then. 'Cos compensation wasn't much you kno
w then. In terms of shillings that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you remember having to go without anything else, to tighten up a little bit during these times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye. Aye. I don't whether my mother didn't start work a bit while me father was on compensation. Aye, in
 a factory you know. Help out - well I think that's how - that's how we managed then. My father'd look after us see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How long was he at home during this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh he was at home about twelve month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What happened, was he injured?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, he
 got this eye darkness. They used to have what they called eye darkness colliers had you know. Of course since they've had these electric lamps and electric in the mines you never hear talk of it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But the colliery paid him compensation because it was their fault his eyes were bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It was very prevalent in them days, eye darkness was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever get help from the parish or any charity at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I don't think so, can never remember it, not to being on parish. I can never remember my mother going to pawnshop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 A lot of people did did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh they did. They used to send a suit of clothes - used to wear them on the Sunday, they used to be in the pawnshop on Monday. I can never remember my mother going there, never. There was very few as didna go you know in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you remember there being anyone at all in your district of whom people strongly disapproved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember hearing talk of anyone that was strongly disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I can't, no I can't. No. Not worth talking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember hearing of anyone being made to leave a particular afea by rough music or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No, I can remember them doing moonlight flits, what they used to call moonlight flits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well if they hadna used to pay their rent, they used to get up in the middle of the night and shift all their furniture and off. You could go into a house anytime there you know. There was always some empty houses about
. But they'd run a few weeks rent up and then they'd be off, and the landlord wouldn't find them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So the landlord really stood to lose a fair amount of money didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Oh that was done very often that was in them days. But they used to cal
l then midnight flits. There again, if you'd get any debts on - debts on used to call what they called the bailiffs to the house. Aye, and they used to mark everything up in the house in value and - off it went. Pay the debts, they used to leave you nothi
n
g in the house. They always put the word out when the bailiffs were about you know. Then they would lock the doors so he couldn't get in. Oh aye, they used to lock the doors and he couldn't get in. We never had - we never had any occasion to have the bunk
s for all that, not at our house. But there was lots as did. And they used to lock the houses up that they couldn't get in, they used to get the tip off when he's about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Can you ever remember anyone having an effigy made of them for any reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Ah what? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you don't remember people trying to move other people for one reason or another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Can't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you given lessons by your parents, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Three years old when I went. Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Wasn't that a bit young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh they used to get 'em off at two or three then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When you first started school what time of the morning did you have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 About - I'd come home at dinnertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What time would you come home at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 About twelve. Go back - two. This is when I first started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you did a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did a full day, yes, when I was three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It finished at three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What kind of school was it, was it a board school or a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Elementary school. Ordinary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Walk it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How long did it take you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh it was only about - five minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who used to go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You used to come home for your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you come home for lunch the whole time you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I never had any trouble with school. I never had a lot of trouble. I wasn't a troublesome - be sent to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you say that you liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh well, I couldn't say that I liked it - but - I was never no trouble get to school anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you feel about your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh I used to respect them, frightened to death of them you know. Oh aye. Aye, used to respect your teachers - I think you respected teachers more than they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life, like manners, tidiness, punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What do you think they put the greatest emphasis on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I should think obedience. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If you did something that the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well some teachers you had in some classes caned their own pupils. But there's certain teachers in other classes never caned them, sent them to the headmaster to be camed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of things would you be caned for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh all sorts of - playing at marbles and - talking during lessons and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they punish the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Couldn't say. I think the girls did have the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I shouldna think - I shouldna say that - I shouldna think too much. As long as you went and come back that was enough for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did they ask you what you did at school or ever visit the school and meet your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I don't think the - parents used to meet teachers in them days, not a lot anyway. I can never remember my parents going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did the other children in the school come from similar types of home as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Now biggest part of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you ever remember any of the teachers singling out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No, can't say I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there any gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you remember any of the children being left out of anything by the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, I shouldna think so. At playtime everybody seemed to join in all games as they had. I'm saying in playtime, the lads'd had a little rubber ball, there'd be perhaps forty or fifty playing with it all at the same time. Aye. Running
 about 'til time we were in school with this little rubber ball, footballing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I did. I won what they call a scholarship when I was twelve. Well I started to Queensbury Road then which is higher el
ementary see. But this - when I went to this school I should have stopped at least I was fourteen, 'cos you left at thirteen then. But as soon as I was thirteen me mother wouldna let me - me mother wouldna let me go any longer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How old were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The elementary school that was. Twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was that also a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. Boys school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That was a higher school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you get that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I had to walk every foot and that was - well you know where Cranbury Road is from here don't you, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How long would you say it took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh be about ten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who went with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I went myself then at twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 At school. Used to take sandwiches from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What sort of sandwiches would you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh perhaps cheese sandwiches, corned beef. Used to boil a lot of beef in that - boiled beef, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I l
iked it. Oh we used to have a lot of different things there. Used to be a woodwork class you know, a chemistry class - mathematics class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Which there wasn't in the other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you enjoyed that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, it was all right. I'd liked to have stopped to I'd been fourteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you think of the teachers at this new school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They're all right. Never had any trouble with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What would they emphasise as being the most important thing in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I can't - I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would they put any emphasis on manners or tidiness or punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, they didn't put any emphasis on the way you spoke, you speak just the same, just ordinary. No, I couldna - couldna put a finger on -
 I couldn't put a finger on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How would you say the teachers expected you to behave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh same as I say, always respected the teachers, what they said was law. I never think - used to think of arguing the point with the teachers. What they sai
d was it. But - the headmaster didna want me to leave that school at thirteen. Aye, he said it was a contract for stop 'til fourteen. I had a hell of a job to get - get away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did the teachers at that school if you did something that they disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Just the same as the ordinary school, you had to have the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork at this other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did they think about you winning this scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well they just go
 as a matter of form, they didn't know I was put in for it. Just told them as a matter of form I got this scholarship and I - I went in this school but - it was worse for myself really, all that walk, especially in winter time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Could you have stayed on at your other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would all the children at this school have had to have won scholarships to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. To go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were they from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were any of the children there singled out for different treatment by the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there any gangs or groups in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there any of the boys there that were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. They all used to join in the sports what was going. Cr
icket or football. Any games as they played - remember nobody being left out. Only them that didn't want to play of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Is that where you actually finished your schooling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That's where I finished. Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And you didn't want to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I'd have gone on 'til I'd been fourteen if I could. But you see my parents wouldna let me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you would have stayed longer had you had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. They wanted that - two or three shillings I could earn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Any evening classes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I do really. I'd have liked that other twelve month for a start. Because I - I never classed myse
lf as a dud, I thought myself I - I'm one of the bright 'uns for me age. Well I was the only one that went there from that school that year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 The only one that won the scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That year, yes. I think another - I think another twelve month at school done me no harm at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think you'd have stood a chance of a better job if you'd -- carried on for that extra year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So the regrets you have are that you didn't stay on longer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Aye. 'Course in them days - the chief subjects you know were reading, writing and arithmetic. Then they tried half an hour geography lesson, half an hour history lesson. But they - they concentrated on them three 
more than anything. Well I think they ought to concentrate more on them even to this day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 While you were still at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I was always doing odd jobs, selling papers, I'd go round selling oatcakes and pikelets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you get these jobs, how did you get your paper round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well it weren't really a paper - I used to go down the Sentinel office - let's see, I'm just thinking how much those papers used to be the
n.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Could anyone just go down to the Sentinel office and sell papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, and buy 'em. Yes, buy 'em from the Sentinel office, they used to be three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
penny, that's what they used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have to buy them in order to sell them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
You bought 'em in a - they used to be three a penny and - every three you sold you made a ha'penny see. Might perhaps have nine papers or a dozen papers. Well was running round the street and sell them, perhaps made - say you had a dozen you'd make tup
pence wouldn't you. This is at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How many hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 We used to run round streets 'til we got shot of the lot. It's just according how they sold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What else did you do as well as sell papers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I used to sell oatca
kes and pikelets. Me father started making them when he was on compensation at pits. Aye, always used to reckon make the rent out of them Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever have a part time job where you actually had to go and work for somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. Same as I say I used to take - dinner - and all. Yes. We've had that I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Could you tell me about your first full time job and what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 My first full time job was mould running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Applied for it - applied for at at the offices at the factory, Cartwright and Edwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I used to work for - a maker as makes saucers. Well the moulder - of course only thirteen, want a very - used to have these two moulds out of the stove - put 'em on the bench and he could get a fat piece of clay and chu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 ck it on, then mould it into sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ers. Then you had to run back with them in a red hot stove. Take them two then make twenty more like see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh
 they used to be real quick these makers had you know. Used to be red hot at night time. What hours? Half past seven 'til half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How many days a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Six days - five days them hours then Saturdays, half past seven 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 We didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What were you paid for this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Five and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you think it was fair?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well we did at that time, five and six was a lot of money, specially for a lad thirteen. But it was heavy work for a lad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Used to give it to her all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did she give you any back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Used to have sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What would you spend that sixpence on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Going pictures or the theatre. Perhaps sneak five fags out of it for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh yes. Where I worked there was a great big shop there about - about forty makers in that shop and some made cups, some made plates, some mad
e these saucers. And they'd all got a lad you know, running moulds for 'em. Oh used to be hard work. I've had me feet bleed of a night time you know. 'Cos it's hot. Ah it wanted stopping that did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you feel about your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh he treated me w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 ell and - the bloke as made sauc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ers as I worked for, as paid me, he treated me well. I used to have many a three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
pence off him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So the chap that you made the saucers for paid your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not the person that owned the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh no. My wages come out of his. He was on piecework see. He used to - he was on piecework. Well they - they used to treat us to the pictures many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So he was a good man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Aye, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you feel about doing this sort of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I - I didn't mind what I felt as long as I was doing good at home, I was thinking about home more than that. But I - I will say this, it's dam}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ed hard work for a lad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you say that you liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well - no, I shouldna say as I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did this job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. 'Course these lads as went in these jobs you know, these - this mould running job, they never used to keep on on 'em - hardly above twelve month. 'Cos then - when they're fourteen - he can apply to the colliery for a job see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How long did you stay doing this particular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well I did that job - I was thirteen in the May and it was the following October before I got a job so - that's May to May, twelve month, June, July
, August - I'd be on the factory about eighteen month before I could get a job at the colliery. Still we had bits of rises during that time. I think I finished up getting about seven shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 That was good was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you actually do when you started at the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Well the first job I had at the colliery was pumping water out of a hand pump. Used to be in stages then and then you used to go - with a bloke, used to call him a day clean, used to clean the air
 holes out see. After that used to go pony driving. Down the mine itself driving a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
pony pulling loads about. And then you'd go work on what they called taking off from the - bottom of the gangway. Then you - that was your last job on the haulage. And then from there if you wanted you'd go either loading or on the coal face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you still working in the pit in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes. Aye. I was there 'til 1946. You know that - that job you had - when you first started in the pits you know, you - I - my wag
es jumped from seven shillings to twelve. That was the rate of pay then, twelve shilling a week. Six days. Oh I thought that was a - a real good job. Aye, that's when it - it - what it used to be, twelve shilling a week when I first started. That'd be in 
- 19 - 1916 wouldn't it. 1902 I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What jobs have you done since the first world war}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 
? You stayed at the colliery 'ti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 l 1946?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 1946. Then I had accident, I had to get out. Then I went with British Railways. And I was there 'til me - 'til I fi
nished altogether. Them are the only two jobs I ever had. Thirty years in the colliery. And eighteen years on British Rail.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have to retire from British Rail because of ill health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you have preferred another type of occupation, what would you have liked to have done preferably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I don't think - it was more me ambition get in the collieries. Just for the sake of the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever serve an apprenticeship or a training period for any of your mobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 N
o. Well - it's - that's - that's what - where the collieries made a mistake. It was an apprenticeship in the - in the coal mine because every - any Tom, Dick and Harry couldn't have gone on the coal face and got coal and looked after himself, the roof and
 that - but it was never classed as a trade, colliery work wasn't. That was - that was the big - biggest mistake as the unions ever made. But it was a trade and it's still trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes, miners union and the - National Union of the Railways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No, just paid me subs and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same interests or different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I didn't think ther
e was much good feeling between employers and employers at that - at that period of my working life. No, the - the workers always seem resentful somehow or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers, people say that 
in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
They never - they never regarded as craftsmen the colliery wasn't. He hadn't got - he hadn't got what you could call a trade, wasn't a trade. And yet it was a trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Apart from the colliery would you say trained craftsmen felt they were different from other workers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh I should. Anybody as served apprenticeship - seemed to be classed higher than a collier in any case. If he was a joiner, a bricklayer. Tha
t was classed above a collier. Anybody with a trade was. And yet that was a real skilled trade, colliery work was. Well in my opinion it was and in thousands of there opinions. But was never classed as one not while I was working in the collieries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you feel any different after you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Felt more independent. 'Course - during the first world war you know - colliers didn't do too bad at all, n
ot from 1918. Lloyd George said, give 'em everything as they want. I remember - the colliers wage was up to a guinea a day in 1918-19. Guinea a day. Had a lot of rises then. And things were very cheap then you know. Yes, cigarettes and that four}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 pence }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13058518\charrsid10123639 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So would you have considered yourself well off at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh we were. But it didn't last long. That's when the trouble started about 1921 we'd colliers strike. And it went to 1926. And that twenty-six week strike then. I think it cripple
d everything. But - we did no work. From about - from then on - when we went back in 1960 - 1926 - our wages dropped from a guinea right down to twelve and six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 A day - we had been out of work then for twenty-six week. Was from then o
n - in about 1928 or '09 they come down to nine shilling a day. But it never come less than that, not in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How did you cope with all these many weeks of unemployment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well there used to be soup kitchens and - all kinds of things about. Bu
t - this district where we are - North Staffordshire, one of the most fortunate of all, colliers. 'Cos they did a lot of outcropping. We had never ought to have done it but we did do it. But theres some at Essex and Wales and Yorkshire where they've got n
o outcrop at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What is outcropping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Digging holes down about - five or six feet. Yes. Oh yes, oh used to do real well. That's while we were on strike.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you do with the coal you outcropped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Sold it to these power stations and - some factory's would buy it. Oh we'd no trouble in selling it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about the unions attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh the union begged and prayed of us stop outcropping but - they wouldn't in this district, you're on to a good thing. They'm getting about twenty
 pound a week. In those days. There's a little place at Cheadle, just - outside the potteries - and I can remember writing on the placards - they used to put placards outside the newsagents shops you know - Cheadle, the richest town in England. That was h
e outcropping town. I worked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How much money did you make in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - about - I was on about fifteen or sixteen pound a week I was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you still giving money to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh aye. Giving money to mother - I'd go
t plenty - plenty of my own. I tell you, everything was cheap, food and everything. Food, drink, cigarettes. We were little millionaires. But some of them in Wales and Yorkshire and Lancashire got - hadna got these outcrops, they must have suffered terrib
le. I can remember our union secretary coming back of the - they used to have that fairground down Longton. MR. A.J. Cook. He went on his bended hands and knees for tell us stop this outcropping. But we didna do. No,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid135701\charrsid10123639  they didna do. It was going agai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135701\charrsid10123639 st - going agai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135701\charrsid10123639 st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  what we were striking for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What were you striking for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Striking for more money. Because it - it kept dropping the wages. Gradually see. And we wanted stop it but it didna stop it. It }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid135701\charrsid10123639 spiralled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  down less than ever see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 This twenty week strike was a long long time really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
It was. And the weather - the weather was gorgeous all the time. If it hadn't have been there's been some of us killed in this outcropping. They used to prop it up with little - those little creech
 sticks, anything. If it hadn't been good weather - been bad weather I'm sure somebody would have been killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there soup kitchens and the like in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I think there was. But I - I never went to one. I think you could get a bowl of soup or anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you didn't suffer much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. 'Course there's a lot of - with us being on strike fetched all potters and everything - pottery workers and - a lot out besides us you know. But - this money is that easy for - well wouldn't stop d
oing it. And they did it right up to the end of the strike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did starting full time work change your relationship you're your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or with your brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, no different. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What were your views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When R was young like? Well I should think I'd have Labour views.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 For what reason particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Because I was a - because I was really a labourer I suppose. Me father was a working - a Labour man. But I didn't follow - follow the lead blindly I'll tell you that. I could see what was wr
ong with that - Conservative and Labour and all, there's faults on both sided. But I was never interested in it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Or to be a member of a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 From your employer for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were you a member of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, I wasn't a member. I'll tell you what used to happen. That colliery as I worked at - it was always said and I think there's some truth it in in the early days I was working. If you was a Methodist, you could get a plum job at that colliery. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So there was religious discrimination of one sort or another then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Well it was - it was always thought by a good many. And I think it
 was true. If you're a good Methodist you could get the plum job at that colliery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Why do you suppose that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Because the owners was big Methodists. It weren't nationalized then, it was privately owned of course. Aye, big Methodists the owners
 were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about people working at the colliery that weren't Methodists, what would happen to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well nothing happened particularly but - in them days they used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4809265\charrsid10123639 
have a - a booty system, this boo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 ty system was like - bloke taking a contract
 and - the contractors used to attend the Methodist chapel they always used to seem to get the best contracts Of course they earned the most money then see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Do you think the fact that you were a Methodist helped you get on in the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, I was not that big a Methodist. You've got attend that chapel. - Oh it only happened to a few you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But it did happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. That was in them days. I can understand - I can understand a bit of this trouble in Northern Ireland. Because a lot of
 that I think is religious trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You don't particularly think of it occurring the collieries do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. But I think it used to occur in the potteries and all. Same as church going people - especially if - those as owned 'em. I think there's a lot of it about even in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever see anybody particularly that got on well because he was of a particular religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 How would he be different from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well same as I say, they'd have a plum contracting
 job, a job as couldn't fail hardly. 'Cos these contractors used to employ perhaps eight or nine men, that contractor'd pay 'em out at the weekend you know. And he'd have what was left. Times it'd be three or four times more than what his - his workmen ha
d. Well that did definitely happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you still go to chapel when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Oh I attended chapel 'til about sixty year I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you still go three times a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No, I went at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you spend your Sundays any differently once you'd started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, no different. Used to be a gang of us out footballing Sunday mornings, perhaps a walk Sunday afternoon. Then we used to go jay walking at night round the town or up - up Trentam. That was a town u
sed to be packed Sunday nights you know, the girls and youths promenading. And all the way to Longton Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 It was a regular thing to do was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Every Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You told me earlier something about how you used to spend your spare t
ime, did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you start dong things differently now that you were earning a bit of extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well same as I say, this promenading round, meeting girls and all that kind of thing. Then when I 
were about seventeen I think I take me first drink. Used to slip in this pub, have perhaps two or three pints then we'd go on this - trip round the town or - promenade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What did you feel like after you'd had your first drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh - I felt a bit merry perhaps. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you go out in the evenings still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
Oh I used to go to the pictures or - the theatre. 'Course then - when I was about seventeen, course I wasn't on the coal face but - at that time I was 
getting about sixteen shillings a day. When I was about seventeen. Oh I did well, I wasn't short of money for a year or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Who did you go out with in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh used to be perhaps in company of four or five youths. Same as I said, go rou
nd - Saturday we'd go to the pictures, then come out of there, perhaps we'd have a drink and do this prom - promenading round the town. Oh and that's how - that carried on for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Was it a Sunday night walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Sunday night and Saturday. Aye, an
d there'd be - there'd be some went round in the week and all. But - in - recently you never see a soul in the town. They've all got different interests.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But it used to be quite crowded?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh it used to be crowded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Now that you were going to work did you make any new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about the young youths at the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well I - biggest part of them were school friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They were friends anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 What about girlfriends, did you have any special girlfriends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh never had no special girlfriend. Used to get chatting 'em up and larking with 'em but - nothing serious.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 If you went out to meet friends how did you meet them and where would you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh I'd always got a meeting
 place. Or we went round their houses and fetch 'em out. Aye. Just knock on door, say, are you coming out tonight? And that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you ever take any of these friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Not girls. No, I never used to take the girls home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 But you took the boys home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Ye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4809265\charrsid10123639 s. We used to go in one another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639  homes. Take no notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did you have any particular friend at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No particular friend at all. Used to go about in fives and sixes and gangs more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 And you were quite happy with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 When you went out in the gangs where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Well if it's Saturday night we'd go to the pictures or somewhere like that and then same as I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4809265\charrsid10123639  say, we'd come out and have a d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 rink and do this larking round town. It happened for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. And their parents. We all come - we all practically come out of same street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 You had virtually been friends all your lives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Yes. Or round the neighbourhood you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your parents still expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No, my parents didn't. When I went out - my - our front door was never locked. Right up to time as I got married it was never locked to the last one was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Did your mother wait up for you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
No. No, just left the door open. You kept coming in one by one and the last one'd close. Oh - come in all hours of the morning. We never had to knock anybody up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Didn't you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. They did in some homes you know. But into in my home. No. They used trust us to get back safe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 So you had a pretty free rein did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4809265\charrsid10123639 Oh aye, I had a pretty free rei}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 
n. I did have a free rein. Nay, there were no question where we'd been either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 They weren't concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No, chance what time we come in. They never used to bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were there any social activities of any sort organised by the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 No. No. You simply went work and when you finished work that was
 it. Well it had a union rally about once a year. Aye, they used - got to Rudyard - they used to go to miners demonstration. Aye, thousands on 'em used to meet in them days. Used to happen about once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13263722 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Were these demonstrations orderly?
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid13263722 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3288297 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7406736\charrsid10123639 Oh yes. Yes. Aye, pick a spot where there gong and they used to gather there, get there any road as we could. Aye, they were quite orderly.

